# What file contains the RSA keys of systems that are authorized to connect via SSH?

# https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/
# how-to-configure-ssh-key-based-authentication-on-a-linux-server

# After generating a key with ssh-keygen,I need to copy the key to the
# remote SSH server by using ssh-copy-id username@remote_host e.g. user@debian
# then we can see the authorized key by using

cat ~/.ssh/authorized_keys